{
  "id": "S2P05M30",
  "title": {
    "product_var": "ZPRODTSK",
    "text": "HOW TO RECORD A KEY MACRO",
    "version_var": "ZSHRTVER",
    "prefix": "HELP"
  },
  "type": "help",
  "body": {
    "rows": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "variable": "ZCMD"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "A key macro is recorded by hitting a key assigned to the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "[KEY-MACRO-RECORD] terminal function, which is assigned to Alt-M"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "by default.  Hitting Alt-M brings up a panel which enables to"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "name and describe the macro to be recorded.  It is similar to:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "MACRO NAME ===>"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "DESCRIPTION ==>"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Macro name is used to identify which macros are assigned to"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "which keys, and description is a comment field.  For example,"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "if we were to assign a COMMBOX macro that inserts a C"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "comment-box into source code, we could fill in the fields as"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "follows:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "MACRO NAME ===> COMMBOX"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "DESCRIPTION ==> Inserts Comment Box in \"C\" Source"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "field_row",
        "fields": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "(Press"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "ENTER+to continue)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
